            "Next first difference: $12+4=16$",
            "Pattern 5: $25+16=41$"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "questionText": "Find an expression for the $n$th term of this sequence.",
          "marks": 4,
          "commandWord": "find",
          "answerType": "expression",
          "correctAnswer": "$2n^2 - 2n + 1$",
          "tolerance": null,
          "unit": null,
          "markScheme": [
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Second differences are constant (4), so quadratic with $a = 2$" },
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Form $2n^2 + bn + c$; use $n=1$: $2+b+c=1$" },
            { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$b=-2$, $c=1$ found correctly" },
            { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$2n^2-2n+1$ cao" }
          ],
          "workingSteps": [
            "Second differences = 4, so $a = \\frac{4}{2} = 2$",
            "Form $2n^2+bn+c$",
            "$n=1$: $2+b+c=1 \\Rightarrow b+c=-1$",
            "$n=2$: $8+2b+c=5 \\Rightarrow 2b+c=-3$",
            "Subtract: $b=-2$; $c=-1-(-2)=1$",
            "$n$th term: $2n^2-2n+1$",
            "Check $n=3$: $2(9)-6+1=18-5=13$ ✓; $n=4$: $2(16)-8+1=25$ ✓"
          ]
        },
